        <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
            <t:abstract>
                <t:p>
                    Any literary work /text which has been added to the manuscript as an additional note, in part (excerpts) or in entirety. It can be a small size or even mid-size composition (frequently malkǝʾ).
                    Typical cases are works written on guard leaves, sometimes even in the reversed direction or transgressing the codicological settings of the main texts in any different way. 
                </t:p>
                <t:p>Examples are:
                    <t:list>
                        <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdmd003">Gāntā ʾAfašum, Dǝblā Yoḥannǝs Maṭmǝq, DMD-003</t:ref>, f. 1r-2v: Malkәʾa Ṗeṭros wa-Ṗāwlos followed by an ʾarke-hymn, in a Four Gospel manuscript; the same text in 
                            <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESath002">Gulo Maḵadā, ʾArāʿro Takla Hāymānot, ATH-002</t:ref>, Acts of Takla Haymanot.</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                        <t:item>
                     <t:p>Synaxarion entries, Creed of faith, theological treatises, dispersed miracles (<t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd025">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi, DD-025</t:ref>, f. 165rv), hymns of the prefactory part
                        of the miracles of Mary, Old Amharic compositions:</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                        <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd025">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi, DD-025</t:ref>, f. 180rv;</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                        <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESakm020">Gulo Maḵadā, ʾAmbasat Kidāna Mǝḥrat, AKM-020</t:ref>, f. 1v-2r, 31r-34v;</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                        <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESma001">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, ʾĀndel Qǝddǝst Māryām, MA-001</t:ref>, despite the fact that the additional texts are written in calligraphic hands;</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                        <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESky023">ʾƎndartā, Koholo Yoḥannǝs Dabra Betel, KY-023</t:ref>, Psalter with an Amharic treatise on the Creation.</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                    </t:list>
            </t:p>
